<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10721&amp;p=123048#p123048"><![CDATA[
I think they should've ran the CPU and PPU on a synchronized 32-bit bus with cartridge pinouts, and 128kB of shared RAM.  The only downside would be screen resolution being tied to CPU speed and ROM latency, but other than that, it would be so much more flexible.  It would be able to fetch sprite patterns directly from the ROM, without any complicated sprite management, and will be better equipped for enhancement chips.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4383">psycopathicteen</a> — Sun Dec 29, 2013 4:38 pm</p><hr />
