<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10721&amp;p=123012#p123012</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10721&amp;p=123012#p123012"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Nobody ever had problems with the NES cpu?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10721&amp;p=123012#p123012"><![CDATA[
The address bus is only guaranteed to be correct by the time φ2 rises, but in practice the transitions happen very shortly after the start of φ1. Most ROMs' /OE-to-data time is half that of their /CE-to-data time, so as long as /CE is only derived from the address bus on the TG16 (and not M2), I would think a plain 120ns ROM should work fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sat Dec 28, 2013 6:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
