I always thought of DMA as read on one half-cycle, write on the other. You can't be sure that the data coming out of the source is correct until the end of the read half-cycle, and the value needs to be held on the data bus during the write half-cycle.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 25, 2013 2:23 pm</p><hr />
